      {
        "name": "Fortune *Bonded Pair*",
        "species": "Dog",
        "breed": "American Bulldog",
        "age": "9 yr",
        "gender": "Female",
        "bio": "My name is Fortune and if you ask me, I'd say your luck is about to change. I'm the mother in a mother/daughter pair and we're hoping to find our new home together; it's all we've ever known. Sure, we have our tiffs and don't always see eye to eye, but family is all you have in this world and we'll always have each other's backs. I like to keep my circle small and am a little hesitant when it comes to meeting new people but I know that in order to get out of the shelter, I have to get out of my shell. I can be social with other dogs when I'm one on one but may be a little more stand-offish when Buttercup is around. I'm not interested in sharing my home with cats and I have had some interaction with children. I struggled to adjust to the shelter when I first got here and I'm sure there'll be a few growing pains in the process of meeting and moving in with a new family, but I'm going to try my hardest to be brave, bold and beautiful.Less",
        "photo": "https://media.adoptapet.com/image/upload/c_auto,g_auto,w_400,ar_4:3,dpr_2/f_auto,q_auto/1198379013",
        "url": "https://www.adoptapet.com/pet/43104948-wausau-wisconsin-american-bulldog-mix"
